<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Nehemiah 7:1-73</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="13">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="73">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And it came about that, as soon as the wall had been rebuilt, I at once set up the doors. Then there were appointed the gatekeepers and the singers and the Levites.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And I went on to put in command of Jerusalem Ha&middot;na&acute;ni my brother and Han&middot;a&middot;ni&acute;ah the prince of the Castle, for he was such a trustworthy man and feared the [true] God more than many others.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">So I said to them: “The gates of Jerusalem should not be opened until the sun gets hot; and while they are standing by they should shut the doors and bolt [them]. And station guards of the inhabitants of Jerusalem, each one at his own guardpost and each one in front of his own house.”</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Now the city was wide and great, and there were few people inside it, and there were no houses built.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">But my God put [it] into my heart that I should collect together the nobles and the deputy rulers and the people to get themselves enrolled genealogically. Then I found the book of genealogical enrollment of those who came up at the first, and found written in it:</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">These are the sons of the jurisdictional district who came up out of the captivity of the exiled people whom Neb&middot;u&middot;chad&middot;nez&acute;zar the king of Babylon had taken into exile and who later returned to Jerusalem and to Judah, each to his own city;</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">those who came in with Ze&middot;rub&acute;ba&middot;bel, Jesh&acute;u&middot;a, Ne&middot;he&middot;mi&acute;ah, Az&middot;a&middot;ri&acute;ah, Ra&middot;a&middot;mi&acute;ah, Na&middot;ham&acute;a&middot;ni, Mor&acute;de&middot;cai, Bil&acute;shan, Mis&acute;pe&middot;reth, Big&acute;vai, Ne&acute;hum, Ba&acute;a&middot;nah.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs7-2">The number of the men of the people of Israel:</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">The sons of Pa&acute;rosh, two thousand one hundred and seventy-two;</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">the sons of Sheph&middot;a&middot;ti&acute;ah, three hundred and seventy-two;</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">the sons of A&acute;rah, six hundred and fifty-two;</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">the sons of Pa&acute;hath-mo&acute;ab, of the sons of Jesh&acute;u&middot;a and Jo&acute;ab, two thousand eight hundred and eighteen;</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">the sons of E&acute;lam, a thousand two hundred and fifty-four;</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">the sons of Zat&acute;tu, eight hundred and forty-five;</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">the sons of Zac&acute;cai, seven hundred and sixty;</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">the sons of Bin&acute;nu&middot;i, six hundred and forty-eight;</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">the sons of Be&acute;bai, six hundred and twenty-eight;</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">the sons of Az&acute;gad, two thousand three hundred and twenty-two;</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">the sons of Ad&middot;o&middot;ni&acute;kam, six hundred and sixty-seven;</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">the sons of Big&acute;vai, two thousand and sixty-seven;</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">the sons of A&acute;din, six hundred and fifty-five;</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">the sons of A&acute;ter, of Hez&middot;e&middot;ki&acute;ah, ninety-eight;</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">the sons of Ha&acute;shum, three hundred and twenty-eight;</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">the sons of Be&acute;zai, three hundred and twenty-four;</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">the sons of Ha&acute;riph, a hundred and twelve;</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">the sons of Gib&acute;e&middot;on, ninety-five;</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">the men of Beth&acute;le&middot;hem and Ne&middot;to&acute;phah, a hundred and eighty-eight;</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">the men of An&acute;a&middot;thoth, a hundred and twenty-eight;</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">the men of Beth-az&acute;ma&middot;veth, forty-two;</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">the men of Kir&acute;i&middot;ath-je&acute;a&middot;rim, Che&middot;phi&acute;rah and Be&middot;er&acute;oth, seven hundred and forty-three;</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">the men of Ra&acute;mah and Ge&acute;ba, six hundred and twenty-one;</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">the men of Mich&acute;mas, a hundred and twenty-two;</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">the men of Beth&acute;el and A&acute;i, a hundred and twenty-three;</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">the men of the other Ne&acute;bo, fifty-two;</span> <a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">the sons of the other E&acute;lam, a thousand two hundred and fifty-four;</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">the sons of Ha&acute;rim, three hundred and twenty;</span> <a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">the sons of Jer&acute;i&middot;cho, three hundred and forty-five;</span> <a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">the sons of Lod, Ha&acute;did and O&acute;no, seven hundred and twenty-one;</span> <a name="bk38" class="vsAnchor">38</a>
       <span id="vs38">the sons of Se&middot;na&acute;ah, three thousand nine hundred and thirty.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk39" class="vsAnchor">39</a>
       <span id="vs39">The priests: The sons of Je&middot;da&acute;iah of the house of Jesh&acute;u&middot;a, nine hundred and seventy-three;</span> <a name="bk40" class="vsAnchor">40</a>
       <span id="vs40">the sons of Im&acute;mer, a thousand and fifty-two;</span> <a name="bk41" class="vsAnchor">41</a>
       <span id="vs41">the sons of Pash&acute;hur, a thousand two hundred and forty-seven;</span> <a name="bk42" class="vsAnchor">42</a>
       <span id="vs42">the sons of Ha&acute;rim, a thousand and seventeen.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk43" class="vsAnchor">43</a>
       <span id="vs43">The Levites: The sons of Jesh&acute;u&middot;a, of Kad&acute;mi&middot;el, of the sons of Ho&acute;de&middot;vah, seventy-four.</span> <a name="bk44" class="vsAnchor">44</a>
       <span id="vs44">The singers, the sons of A&acute;saph, a hundred and forty-eight.</span> <a name="bk45" class="vsAnchor">45</a>
       <span id="vs45">The gatekeepers, the sons of Shal&acute;lum, the sons of A&acute;ter, the sons of Tal&acute;mon, the sons of Ak&acute;kub, the sons of Ha&middot;ti&acute;ta, the sons of Sho&acute;bai, a hundred and thirty-eight.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk46" class="vsAnchor">46</a>
       <span id="vs46">The Neth&acute;i&middot;nim: The sons of Zi&acute;ha, the sons of Ha&middot;su&acute;pha, the sons of Tab&middot;ba&acute;oth,</span> <a name="bk47" class="vsAnchor">47</a>
       <span id="vs47">the sons of Ke&acute;ros, the sons of Si&acute;a, the sons of Pa&acute;don,</span> <a name="bk48" class="vsAnchor">48</a>
       <span id="vs48">the sons of Le&middot;ba&acute;nah, the sons of Hag&acute;a&middot;bah, the sons of Sal&acute;mai,</span> <a name="bk49" class="vsAnchor">49</a>
       <span id="vs49">the sons of Ha&acute;nan, the sons of Gid&acute;del, the sons of Ga&acute;har,</span> <a name="bk50" class="vsAnchor">50</a>
       <span id="vs50">the sons of Re&middot;a&acute;iah, the sons of Re&acute;zin, the sons of Ne&middot;ko&acute;da,</span> <a name="bk51" class="vsAnchor">51</a>
       <span id="vs51">the sons of Gaz&acute;zam, the sons of Uz&acute;za, the sons of Pa&middot;se&acute;ah,</span> <a name="bk52" class="vsAnchor">52</a>
       <span id="vs52">the sons of Be&acute;sai, the sons of Me&middot;u&acute;nim, the sons of Ne&middot;phush&acute;e&middot;sim,</span> <a name="bk53" class="vsAnchor">53</a>
       <span id="vs53">the sons of Bak&acute;buk, the sons of Ha&middot;ku&acute;pha, the sons of Har&acute;hur,</span> <a name="bk54" class="vsAnchor">54</a>
       <span id="vs54">the sons of Baz&acute;lith, the sons of Me&middot;hi&acute;da, the sons of Har&acute;sha,</span> <a name="bk55" class="vsAnchor">55</a>
       <span id="vs55">the sons of Bar&acute;kos, the sons of Sis&acute;e&middot;ra, the sons of Te&acute;mah,</span> <a name="bk56" class="vsAnchor">56</a>
       <span id="vs56">the sons of Ne&middot;zi&acute;ah, the sons of Ha&middot;ti&acute;pha.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk57" class="vsAnchor">57</a>
       <span id="vs57">The sons of the servants of Sol&acute;o&middot;mon: The sons of So&acute;tai, the sons of So&middot;phe&acute;reth, the sons of Pe&middot;ri&acute;da,</span> <a name="bk58" class="vsAnchor">58</a>
       <span id="vs58">the sons of Ja&acute;a&middot;la, the sons of Dar&acute;kon, the sons of Gid&acute;del,</span> <a name="bk59" class="vsAnchor">59</a>
       <span id="vs59">the sons of Sheph&middot;a&middot;ti&acute;ah, the sons of Hat&acute;til, the sons of Po&acute;che&middot;reth-haz&middot;ze&middot;ba&acute;im, the sons of A&acute;mon.</span> <a name="bk60" class="vsAnchor">60</a>
       <span id="vs60">All the Neth&acute;i&middot;nim and the sons of the servants of Sol&acute;o&middot;mon were three hundred and ninety-two.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk61" class="vsAnchor">61</a>
       <span id="vs61">And these were the ones going up from Tel-me&acute;lah, Tel-har&acute;sha, Che&acute;rub, Ad&acute;don and Im&acute;mer, and they were not able to tell the house of their fathers and their origin, whether they were of Israel:</span> <a name="bk62" class="vsAnchor">62</a>
       <span id="vs62">the sons of De&middot;la&acute;iah, the sons of To&middot;bi&acute;ah, the sons of Ne&middot;ko&acute;da, six hundred and forty-two.</span> <a name="bk63" class="vsAnchor">63</a>
       <span id="vs63">And of the priests: the sons of Ha&middot;bai&acute;ah, the sons of Hak&acute;koz, the sons of Bar&middot;zil&acute;lai, who took a wife from the daughters of Bar&middot;zil&acute;lai the Gil&acute;e&middot;ad&middot;ite and came to be called by their name.</span> <a name="bk64" class="vsAnchor">64</a>
       <span id="vs64">These were the ones that looked for their register, to establish their genealogy publicly, and it was not found, so that they were barred as polluted from the priesthood.</span> <a name="bk65" class="vsAnchor">65</a>
       <span id="vs65">Consequently the Tir&middot;sha&acute;tha said to them that they should not eat from the most holy things until the priest with U&acute;rim and Thum&acute;mim stood up.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk66" class="vsAnchor">66</a>
       <span id="vs66">The entire congregation as one group was forty-two thousand three hundred and sixty,</span> <a name="bk67" class="vsAnchor">67</a>
       <span id="vs67">apart from their men slaves and their slave girls, these being seven thousand three hundred and thirty-seven; and they had two hundred and forty-five male singers and female singers. [</span> <a name="bk68" class="vsAnchor">68</a>
       <span id="vs68">Their horses were seven hundred and thirty-six, their mules two hundred and forty-five.]</span> <a name="bk69" class="vsAnchor">69</a>
       <span id="vs69">The camels were four hundred and thirty-five. The asses were six thousand seven hundred and twenty.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk70" class="vsAnchor">70</a>
       <span id="vs70">And there was a part of the heads of the paternal houses that gave to the work. The Tir&middot;sha&acute;tha himself gave to the treasure a thousand gold drachmas, fifty bowls, five hundred and thirty priests’ robes.</span> <a name="bk71" class="vsAnchor">71</a>
       <span id="vs71">And there were some of the heads of the paternal houses that gave to the treasure for the work twenty thousand gold drachmas and two thousand two hundred silver mi&acute;nas.</span> <a name="bk72" class="vsAnchor">72</a>
       <span id="vs72">And what the rest of the people gave was twenty thousand gold drachmas and two thousand silver mi&acute;nas and sixty-seven priests’ robes.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk73" class="vsAnchor">73</a>
       <span id="vs73">And the priests and the Levites and the gatekeepers and the singers and some of the people and the Neth&acute;i&middot;nim and all Israel took up dwelling in their cities. When the seventh month arrived, the sons of Israel were then in their cities.</span>
</p>
</form>

