<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Nehemiah 11:1-36</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="13">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="36">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Now the princes of the people had their dwelling in Jerusalem; but as for the rest of the people, they cast lots to bring in one out of every ten to dwell in Jerusalem the holy city, and the nine other parts in the other cities.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">Moreover, the people blessed all the men who volunteered to dwell in Jerusalem.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And these are the heads of the jurisdictional district who dwelt in Jerusalem; but in the cities of Judah there dwelt, each one in his own possession, in their cities, Israel, the priests and the Levites, and the Neth&acute;i&middot;nim and the sons of the servants of Sol&acute;o&middot;mon.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Also, in Jerusalem there dwelt some of the sons of Judah and some of the sons of Benjamin. Of the sons of Judah there were A&middot;thai&acute;ah the son of Uz&middot;zi&acute;ah the son of Zech&middot;a&middot;ri&acute;ah the son of Am&middot;a&middot;ri&acute;ah the son of Sheph&middot;a&middot;ti&acute;ah the son of Ma&middot;hal&acute;a&middot;lel of the sons of Pe&acute;rez;</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">and Ma&middot;a&middot;sei&acute;ah the son of Bar&acute;uch the son of Col&middot;ho&acute;zeh the son of Ha&middot;zai&acute;ah the son of A&middot;dai&acute;ah the son of Joi&acute;a&middot;rib the son of Zech&middot;a&middot;ri&acute;ah the son of the She&middot;la&acute;nite.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">All the sons of Pe&acute;rez who were dwelling in Jerusalem were four hundred and sixty-eight, capable men.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And these were the sons of Benjamin: Sal&acute;lu the son of Me&middot;shul&acute;lam the son of Jo&acute;ed the son of Pe&middot;dai&acute;ah the son of Ko&middot;lai&acute;ah the son of Ma&middot;a&middot;sei&acute;ah the son of Ith&acute;i&middot;el the son of Je&middot;sha&acute;iah;</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">and after him Gab&middot;ba&acute;i [and] Sal&middot;la&acute;i, nine hundred and twenty-eight;</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">and Joel the son of Zich&acute;ri, an overseer over them, and Judah the son of Has&middot;se&middot;nu&acute;ah over the city as second.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">Of the priests: Je&middot;da&acute;iah the son of Joi&acute;a&middot;rib, Ja&acute;chin,</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">Se&middot;rai&acute;ah the son of Hil&middot;ki&acute;ah the son of Me&middot;shul&acute;lam the son of Za&acute;dok the son of Me&middot;ra&acute;ioth the son of A&middot;hi&acute;tub, a leader of the house of the [true] God;</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">and their brothers the doers of the work of the house, eight hundred and twenty-two; and A&middot;dai&acute;ah the son of Je&middot;ro&acute;ham the son of Pel&middot;a&middot;li&acute;ah the son of Am&acute;zi the son of Zech&middot;a&middot;ri&acute;ah the son of Pash&acute;hur the son of Mal&middot;chi&acute;jah,</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">and his brothers, heads of paternal houses, two hundred and forty-two, and A&middot;mash&acute;sai the son of Az&acute;ar&middot;el the son of Ah&acute;zai the son of Me&middot;shil&acute;le&middot;moth the son of Im&acute;mer,</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">and their brothers, mighty men of valor, a hundred and twenty-eight, and there was an overseer over them, Zab&acute;di&middot;el the son of the great ones.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">And of the Levites: She&middot;mai&acute;ah the son of Has&acute;shub the son of Az&middot;ri&acute;kam the son of Hash&middot;a&middot;bi&acute;ah the son of Bun&acute;ni,</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">and Shab&acute;be&middot;thai and Jo&acute;za&middot;bad, of the heads of the Levites, over the outside business of the house of the [true] God;</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">and Mat&middot;ta&middot;ni&acute;ah himself, the son of Mi&acute;cah the son of Zab&acute;di the son of A&acute;saph, the conductor of the praise [singing], did the lauding at prayer, and Bak&middot;bu&middot;ki&acute;ah was second of his brothers, and Ab&acute;da the son of Sham&middot;mu&acute;a the son of Ga&acute;lal the son of Je&middot;du&acute;thun.</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">All the Levites in the holy city were two hundred and eighty-four.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">And the gatekeepers were Ak&acute;kub, Tal&acute;mon and their brothers who were keeping guard in the gates, a hundred and seventy-two.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">And the rest of Israel, of the priests [and] of the Levites, were in all the other cities of Judah, each one in his own hereditary possession.</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">And the Neth&acute;i&middot;nim were dwelling in O&acute;phel; and Zi&acute;ha and Gish&acute;pa were over the Neth&acute;i&middot;nim.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">And the overseer of the Levites in Jerusalem was Uz&acute;zi the son of Ba&acute;ni the son of Hash&middot;a&middot;bi&acute;ah the son of Mat&middot;ta&middot;ni&acute;ah the son of Mi&acute;ca of the sons of A&acute;saph, the singers, concerning the work of the house of the [true] God.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">For there was a commandment of the king in behalf of them, and there was a fixed provision for the singers as each day required.</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">And Peth&middot;a&middot;hi&acute;ah the son of Me&middot;shez&acute;a&middot;bel of the sons of Ze&acute;rah the son of Judah was at the side of the king for every matter of the people.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">And as regards the settlements in their fields, there were some of the sons of Judah that dwelt in Kir&acute;i&middot;ath-ar&acute;ba and its dependent towns and in Di&acute;bon and its dependent towns and in Je&middot;kab&acute;ze&middot;el and its settlements,</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">and in Jesh&acute;u&middot;a and in Mo&middot;la&acute;dah and in Beth-pel&acute;et</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">and in Ha&acute;zar-shu&acute;al and in Be&acute;er-she&acute;ba and its dependent towns</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">and in Zik&acute;lag and in Me&middot;co&acute;nah and its dependent towns</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">and in En-rim&acute;mon and in Zo&acute;rah and in Jar&acute;muth,</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">Za&middot;no&acute;ah, A&middot;dul&acute;lam and their settlements, La&acute;chish and its fields, A&middot;ze&acute;kah and its dependent towns. And they took up camping from Be&acute;er-she&acute;ba clear to the valley of Hin&acute;nom.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">And the sons of Benjamin were from Ge&acute;ba, Mich&acute;mash and Ai&acute;ja and Beth&acute;el and its dependent towns,</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">An&acute;a&middot;thoth, Nob, A&middot;na&middot;ni&acute;ah,</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">Ha&acute;zor, Ra&acute;mah, Git&acute;ta&middot;im,</span> <a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">Ha&acute;did, Ze&middot;bo&acute;im, Ne&middot;bal&acute;lat,</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">Lod and O&acute;no, the valley of the craftsmen.</span> <a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">And of the Levites there were divisions of Judah for Benjamin.</span>
</p>
</form>

